## Approach: Digit Extraction

Extract digits using modulo 10, build the reversed number. Before each multiplication, check if the result would overflow the 32-bit signed integer range.

```javascript
function reverseInteger(x) {
  let result = 0;
  while (x !== 0) {
    const digit = x % 10;
    x = Math.trunc(x / 10);
    if (result > 2147483647 / 10 || result < -2147483648 / 10) return 0;
    result = result * 10 + digit;
  }
  return result;
}
```

