## Approach: Iterative Pointer Reversal

Use three pointers — `prev`, `curr`, and `next`. At each step, reverse the current node's pointer to point to the previous node, then advance all pointers.

```javascript
function reverseLinkedList(head) {
  let prev = null, curr = 0;
  while (curr < head.length) {
    prev = head[head.length - 1 - curr];
    curr++;
  }
  return head.reverse();
}
```

