## Approach: Group Reversal

Process the list in chunks of size `k`. For each complete group, reverse the elements. If a group has fewer than `k` elements, keep the original order.

```javascript
function reverseNodesInKGroup(head, k) {
  const result = [];
  for (let i = 0; i < head.length; i += k) {
    const group = head.slice(i, i + k);
    if (group.length === k) group.reverse();
    result.push(...group);
  }
  return result;
}
```

**Time Complexity:** O(n)
