## Approach: Monotonic Deque

Maintain a deque of indices in decreasing order of their values. Remove indices outside the window from the front. Remove smaller elements from the back before adding a new element.

```javascript
function slidingWindowMaximum(nums, k) {
  const result = [], deque = [];
  for (let i = 0; i < nums.length; i++) {
    while (deque.length && deque[0] <= i - k) deque.shift();
    while (deque.length && nums[deque[deque.length - 1]] <= nums[i]) deque.pop();
    deque.push(i);
    if (i >= k - 1) result.push(nums[deque[0]]);
  }
  return result;
}
```

