## Approach: BFS

Model the board as a graph. BFS from square 1, trying dice rolls 1-6. Convert square numbers to board coordinates using Boustrophedon indexing. Track visited squares.

```javascript
function snakesAndLadders(board) {
  const n = board.length;
  const getCoords = (s) => {
    const r = Math.floor((s - 1) / n);
    const c = (s - 1) % n;
    return [n - 1 - r, r % 2 === 0 ? c : n - 1 - c];
  };
  const visited = new Set([1]);
  const queue = [[1, 0]];
  while (queue.length) {
    const [curr, moves] = queue.shift();
    for (let d = 1; d <= 6; d++) {
      let next = curr + d;
      if (next > n * n) continue;
      const [r, c] = getCoords(next);
      if (board[r][c] !== -1) next = board[r][c];
      if (next === n * n) return moves + 1;
      if (!visited.has(next)) { visited.add(next); queue.push([next, moves + 1]); }
    }
  }
  return -1;
}
```

**Time Complexity:** O(n²)
**Space Complexity:** O(n²)

