## Approach: Merge Sort

Recursively split the list into halves using slow/fast pointers, sort each half, then merge them. Merge sort naturally fits linked lists due to efficient splitting.

```javascript
function sortList(head) {
  if (head.length <= 1) return head;
  const mid = Math.floor(head.length / 2);
  const left = sortList(head.slice(0, mid));
  const right = sortList(head.slice(mid));
  const result = [];
  let i = 0, j = 0;
  while (i < left.length && j < right.length) {
    if (left[i] <= right[j]) result.push(left[i++]);
    else result.push(right[j++]);
  }
  return result.concat(left.slice(i), right.slice(j));
}
```

**Time Complexity:** O(n log n)
**Space Complexity:** O(log n) recursion stack

