## Approach: Greedy Line Packing

Greedily pack words per line. Distribute spaces evenly, giving extra spaces to leftmost gaps. Last line is left-justified with trailing spaces.

```javascript
function textJustification(words, maxWidth) {
  const result = [];
  let i = 0;
  while (i < words.length) {
    let j = i, lineLen = 0;
    while (j < words.length && lineLen + words[j].length + (j - i) <= maxWidth) {
      lineLen += words[j].length;
      j++;
    }
    const gaps = j - i - 1;
    let line = '';
    if (j === words.length || gaps === 0) {
      line = words.slice(i, j).join(' ');
      line += ' '.repeat(maxWidth - line.length);
    } else {
      const totalSpaces = maxWidth - lineLen;
      const sp = Math.floor(totalSpaces / gaps);
      const extra = totalSpaces % gaps;
      for (let k = i; k < j; k++) {
        line += words[k];
        if (k < j - 1) line += ' '.repeat(sp + (k - i < extra ? 1 : 0));
      }
    }
    result.push(line);
    i = j;
  }
  return result;
}
```

**Time Complexity:** O(n) where n = total characters
**Space Complexity:** O(1) per line

