## Approach: Kirchhoff's Theorem

Build the Laplacian matrix `L = D - A` (degree minus adjacency). Delete any one row and column to get the cofactor matrix. The determinant of this cofactor matrix equals the number of spanning trees.

```javascript
function totalNumberOfSpanningTreesInAGraph(n, edges) {
  const L = Array.from({length: n}, () => new Array(n).fill(0));
  for (const [u, v] of edges) {
    L[u][u]++; L[v][v]++;
    L[u][v]--; L[v][u]--;
  }
  const sz = n - 1;
  const M = Array.from({length: sz}, (_, i) =>
    Array.from({length: sz}, (_, j) => L[i][j])
  );
  let det = 1;
  for (let col = 0; col < sz; col++) {
    let pivot = -1;
    for (let row = col; row < sz; row++) if (M[row][col] !== 0) { pivot = row; break; }
    if (pivot === -1) return 0;
    if (pivot !== col) { [M[col], M[pivot]] = [M[pivot], M[col]]; det *= -1; }
    det *= M[col][col];
    for (let row = col + 1; row < sz; row++) {
      const f = M[row][col] / M[col][col];
      for (let j = col; j < sz; j++) M[row][j] -= f * M[col][j];
    }
  }
  return Math.round(det);
}
```

**Time Complexity:** O(V³)
**Space Complexity:** O(V²)

