## Approach: BFS with Column Tracking

BFS through the tree, tracking each node's (column, row, value). Group by column, sort within groups by row then value.

```javascript
function verticalOrderTraversalOfABinaryTree(root) {
  if (!root.length) return [];
  const map = new Map();
  const queue = [[0, 0, 0]];
  while (queue.length) {
    const [idx, col, row] = queue.shift();
    if (idx >= root.length || root[idx] === null) continue;
    if (!map.has(col)) map.set(col, []);
    map.set(col, [...map.get(col), [row, root[idx]]]);
    queue.push([2*idx+1, col-1, row+1]);
    queue.push([2*idx+2, col+1, row+1]);
  }
  return [...map.keys()].sort((a,b) => a-b)
    .map(col => map.get(col).sort((a,b) => a[0]-b[0] || a[1]-b[1]).map(v => v[1]));
}
```

**Time Complexity:** O(n log n)
**Space Complexity:** O(n)

