## Approach: Sort + DP + Binary Search

Sort jobs by end time. For each job, either skip it or take it (adding its profit to the best non-overlapping result). Use binary search to find the latest non-overlapping job.

```javascript
function weightedJobScheduling(jobs) {
  jobs.sort((a, b) => a[1] - b[1]);
  const n = jobs.length;
  const dp = new Array(n).fill(0);
  dp[0] = jobs[0][2];
  for (let i = 1; i < n; i++) {
    let incl = jobs[i][2];
    let lo = 0, hi = i - 1, last = -1;
    while (lo <= hi) {
      const mid = (lo + hi) >> 1;
      if (jobs[mid][1] <= jobs[i][0]) { last = mid; lo = mid + 1; }
      else hi = mid - 1;
    }
    if (last !== -1) incl += dp[last];
    dp[i] = Math.max(dp[i - 1], incl);
  }
  return dp[n - 1];
}
```

**Time Complexity:** O(n log n)
**Space Complexity:** O(n)

