## Approach: Trie + DP

Build a trie from the dictionary. Use DP where `dp[i]` means `s[0..i-1]` is breakable. For each position, traverse the trie to find matching words and check if the position before the match is breakable.

```javascript
function wordBreakProblemTrieSolution(s, wordDict) {
  const root = {};
  for (const word of wordDict) {
    let node = root;
    for (const ch of word) { if (!node[ch]) node[ch] = {}; node = node[ch]; }
    node.end = true;
  }
  const n = s.length;
  const dp = new Array(n + 1).fill(false);
  dp[0] = true;
  for (let i = 0; i < n; i++) {
    if (!dp[i]) continue;
    let node = root;
    for (let j = i; j < n; j++) {
      if (!node[s[j]]) break;
      node = node[s[j]];
      if (node.end) dp[j + 1] = true;
    }
  }
  return dp[n];
}
```

**Time Complexity:** O(n²) where n = s.length
**Space Complexity:** O(m) for trie, m = total dictionary characters

