## Approach: BFS

BFS from `beginWord`. At each level, try changing each character to a-z. If the new word is in the word set, add it to the queue and remove from the set to avoid revisiting.

```javascript
function wordLadder(beginWord, endWord, wordList) {
  const wordSet = new Set(wordList);
  if (!wordSet.has(endWord)) return 0;
  const queue = [[beginWord, 1]];
  const visited = new Set([beginWord]);
  while (queue.length) {
    const [word, level] = queue.shift();
    for (let i = 0; i < word.length; i++) {
      for (let c = 97; c <= 122; c++) {
        const nw = word.slice(0,i) + String.fromCharCode(c) + word.slice(i+1);
        if (nw === endWord) return level + 1;
        if (wordSet.has(nw) && !visited.has(nw)) {
          visited.add(nw);
          queue.push([nw, level + 1]);
        }
      }
    }
  }
  return 0;
}
```

**Time Complexity:** O(M² × N), M = word length, N = word list size
**Space Complexity:** O(M × N)

